The paper deals with Multi-task Learning (MTL) models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on a more general framework called Conic MTL, which can be applied to various subfields of computer science such as natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the theoretical justification for the Conic MTL method, which is relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new Conic MTL model, which involves optimization techniques that are relevant to the subfield of optimization and control (cs.SI).
